President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 19, 2017, as National Defense Transportation Day and May 14 through May 20, 2017, as National Transportation Week. The proclamation recognizes and celebrates the importance of the nation's land, air, and sea infrastructure systems in connecting Americans, providing national security capabilities, and supporting the economy. The proclamation also acknowledges the efforts of transportation professionals in ensuring the security, efficiency, and reliability of the transportation networks. President Trump emphasizes the need to rebuild the country's transportation infrastructure and remove regulatory hurdles to facilitate necessary improvements. The proclamation highlights the critical role of transportation in national defense and mentions the historical significance of American transportation enhancements during World War II. The president encourages all Americans to participate in appropriate ceremonies and activities to learn more about how the transportation system contributes to the security and prosperity of the nation.